# Code of Conduct for Fossil-Ledger

## Our Pledge
We are committed to making Fossil-Ledger a welcoming and respectful project.  
Contributors and maintainers pledge to create an environment free from harassment, discrimination, and hostility, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, gender identity, sexual orientation, education, experience, nationality, race, religion, or other characteristics.

## Our Standards
**Examples of positive behavior:**
- Using welcoming and inclusive language  
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences  
- Accepting constructive feedback gracefully  
- Focusing on what benefits the community and project  

**Examples of unacceptable behavior:**
- Harassment, trolling, or personal attacks  
- Discriminatory or derogatory comments  
- Publishing othersâ€™ private information without consent  
- Sustained disruption of discussions or contributions  

## Enforcement
- Project maintainers have the right and responsibility to enforce this Code of Conduct.  
- Instances of abusive, harassing, or unacceptable behavior should be reported to:  
  **[INSERT YOUR CONTACT EMAIL HERE]**  
- All complaints will be reviewed and investigated fairly and promptly.  

## Scope
This Code of Conduct applies in all project spaces and interactions, both online and offline, whenever someone represents the project or its community.

## Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org), version 2.1.
